  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support of initiatives that contribute to the implementation and knowledge of the 2005 Convention in the Andean countries</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">There is an increasing request for capacity building and support from governments in order to clarify its objectives and disseminate the 2005 Convention. In addition the relation of culture with sustainable development has called the interest of the States Parties and are willing to work on elaborating policies that will include culture in the national and local agendas. The Culture Sector activities for the biennium will aim at strengthening knowledge on the 2005 Convention in the Andean Cluster, in order to highlight the differences with the other UNESCO Culture Conventions. Additionally, the Culture Sector will provide technical support to Member States in the presentation of projects to the IFCD and the elaboration of quadrennial periodic reports.</narrative>
  </description>
